microtar
------------------------------------------
Lightweight tar library written in ANSI C

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libmicrotar-devel-0.1.0-1bl3
  libmicrotar0-0.1.0-1bl3
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/rxi/microtar

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/rxi/microtar/archive/refs/tags/v0.1.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack microtar-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./microtar-0.1.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/microtar-0.1.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/microtar-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmicrotar0-0.1.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libmicrotar-devel-0.1.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(microtar)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/microtar.README
  /usr/share/doc/microtar/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/microtar/README.md

(libmicrotar0)
  /usr/bin/cygmicrotar-0.dll

(libmicrotar-devel)
  /usr/include/microtar.h
  /usr/lib/libmicrotar.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/microtar.pc

------------------

